cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and event schema induction. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves machine learning techniques. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a joint entity-driven model for learning templates and slots. It may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as event schema induction can be useful in information retrieval tasks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are used in the proposed model.
